+    """

+    
+    :returns: a dict with the content of the ../monitoring.properties file
+    """
+    inProps = FileInputStream(fileName)
+    props = Properties()
+    props.load(inProps)
+    inProps.close()
+    # put props in globals
+    iter = props.entrySet().iterator()
+

+#!/usr/bin/env jython
+from java.lang import Object, Thread, System
+from java.util import Calendar
+from java.io import File, FileOutputStream, PrintWriter
+
+from com.deutschebahn.monitoring import MessageSender,Time 
+from com.deutschebahn.monitoring.Protos import MonitoringMessage
+from com.deutschebahn.monitoring.Protos.MonitoringMessage import MessageSeverity
+
+from weblogic.health import HealthState
+
+import common.utilities
+from common.utilities import toBool
+from scheduler.task import Task
+from scheduler.event import Event
+from scheduler.eventhandler import EventHandler
+from scheduler.deutschebahn.dbeventhandler import DBEventHandler
+from scheduler.deutschebahn.dbevent import DBEvent
+
+from scheduler.weblogic.wlsscheduler import WLSScheduler
+
+import wlstModule as wl
+import sys, traceback
+
+from tasks.serverruntimetask import ServerRuntimeTask
+from tasks.serverlifecycletask import ServerLifeCycleTask
+from tasks.jdbcruntimetask import JDBCRuntimeTask
+from tasks.jtaruntimetask import JTARuntimeTask
+from tasks.jmsruntimetask import JMSRuntimeTask,JMSQuota,DestinationQuota
+from tasks.migratabletargetstask import MigratableTargetsTask
+from tasks.messagebridgeruntimetask import MessageBridgeRuntimeTask
+from tasks.applicationruntimetask import ApplicationRuntimeTask
+
+#===================================================
+# global variables
+#===================================================
+monitoringTimeFile="../scheduler.time"
+
+moduleName="monitor.py"
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#    Usage function
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+def usage():
+    """
+    Print out a usage message for this module
+    """
+    s=[]
+    s.append("####################################################################################")
+    s.append("MODULE: " + moduleName)
+    s.append("        Module used to start monitoring weblogic runtime mbeans")
+    s.append("")
+    s.append("USAGE: wlst "+ moduleName+" command [Options]")
+    s.append("         ")
+    s.append("COMMANDS: execute ")
+    s.append("             Calls the execute Function which start the monitoring process")
+    s.append("         ")
+    s.append("EXAMPLES: java weblogic.WLST " + moduleName + " execute")
+    s.append("         ")
+    s.append("####################################################################################")
+    for item in s:
+        print item
+   #end for
+#end def
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#    Public Interface of this Module
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+def execute(listOptions):
+    """
+    execute Funktion that instantiates a Logger and 
+    then Instantiates the testcases
+    We call the run() method to execute all tests
+
+    :param listOptions: program args
+    """
+    logger = common.utilities.Logger([moduleName, "DBWLSScheduler"]).getLogger()
+    logger.debug("entering ...")
+    logger.debug("Options : %s" % listOptions)
+    logger.debug("Options : %s" % listOptions)
+
+    logger.debug("load properties")
+    dictProps = common.utilities.loadProperties(System.getProperty("monitoring.properties"))
+    
+    # testfaelle laden...    
+    executor = DBWLSScheduler(dictProps)
+    executor.execute()
+#end def
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#    Private and Helper Function of this Modul
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+# CLASSES
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+class DBWLSScheduler(WLSScheduler):
+    """
+    This class is the main class for executing test environment
+    """
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def __init__(self, dictProps):
+        """
+        Constructor for the Executor
+     
+        :param dictProps: dict with properties from monitoring.properties file
+        """
+        WLSScheduler.__init__(self, dictProps)
+        self.logger = common.utilities.Logger([moduleName, "DBWLSScheduler"]).getLogger()
+        self.logger.debug("Executor Constructor")
+    #end
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def initializeTasks(self):
+        """
+        initialises test cases from properties
+        """
+        WLSScheduler.initializeTasks(self)
+        logger = common.utilities.Logger([moduleName, "DBWLSScheduler"]).getLogger()
+        logger.debug("initialize ...")
+
+        if self.dictProps.has_key("scheduler.time.file"): 
+            monitoringTimeFile = self.getProperty("scheduler.time.file")
+        else:
+            logger.warn("No property monitoring.time.file found! Use \"scheduler.time\" as default for storing the current execution time")
+        #end if
+
+        # globale variablen initialisieren
+        self.origin= self.getProperty("scheduler.wls.origin")
+        self.wlsHost=self.getProperty("scheduler.wls.server")
+        self.wlsHostName=self.getProperty("scheduler.wls.hostname")
+        self.wlsPort=self.getProperty("scheduler.wls.port") 
+
+        #quotas erzeugen fuer JMS testing
+        #quotaLogging=toBool(self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.jms.quota")))
+        jmsWarningQuota  = long(self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.jms.warning"))
+        jmsCriticalQuota = long(self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.jms.critical"));
+        jmsWarningQuotaPending  = long(self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.jms.pending.warning"))
+        jmsCriticalQuotaPending = long(self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.jms.pending.critical"));
+
+        queueLogging=toBool(self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.jms.queue.size"))) 
+        queueWarningQuota  = long(self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.jms.queue.warning"))
+        queueCriticalQuota = long(self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.jms.queue.critical"));
+        queueWarningQuotaPending  = long(self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.jms.queue.pending.warning"))
+        queueCriticalQuotaPending = long(self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.jms.queue.pending.critical"))
+        queues = self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.jms.queue.names")
+        queuesIgnore = self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.jms.queue.names.ignore")
+
+        jmsQuota = JMSQuota(1, jmsWarningQuota, jmsCriticalQuota, jmsWarningQuotaPending, jmsCriticalQuotaPending)
+        destinationQuota = DestinationQuota(queueLogging, queueWarningQuota, queueCriticalQuota,queueWarningQuotaPending, queueCriticalQuotaPending, queues)
+
+        # Liste mit Testfaellen intialisieren
+        self.addTask( ServerLifeCycleTask(toBool(self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.server.lifecycle"))))
+        self.addTask( ServerRuntimeTask(toBool(self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.server.runtime"))))
+        self.addTask( JTARuntimeTask(toBool(self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.jta.runtime"))))
+        self.addTask( JMSRuntimeTask(toBool(self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.jms.runtime")), queuesIgnore.split(',') ,jmsQuota, destinationQuota))
+        self.addTask( ApplicationRuntimeTask(toBool(self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.deployments")), self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.deployments.names")))
+        self.addTask( JDBCRuntimeTask(toBool(self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.jdbc.runtime"))))
+        self.addTask( MigratableTargetsTask(toBool(self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.migratabletargets")), self.dictProps))
+        self.addTask( MessageBridgeRuntimeTask(toBool(self.getProperty("scheduler.tasks.messagebridge.runtime"))))
+    #def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def initializeEventHandler(self):
+        """
+        initialises the MessageHandlers
+        """
+        WLSScheduler.initializeEventHandler(self)
+        if (toBool(self.getProperty("scheduler.sendmessages"))):
+            self.addEventHandler(DBEventHandler(self.wlsHostName, self.origin))
+        #end if
+    #end def
+
+
+    #----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def getExecutionErrorEvent(self):
+       return DBEvent("weblogic.jmx.server", self.adminName, "Server.HEALTH", "FAILED", MessageSeverity.ERROR, "Cannot connect to " + self.wlsHostName + ":" + self.wlsPort)
+    #end def
+#end class
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+# MAIN 
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+def main():
+  """
+  parse the command line and execute the command
+  #### the 1st argument is this module
+  #### the 2nd argument should be the command
+  #### the 3rd argument is an options string
+  """
+  logger = common.utilities.Logger([moduleName, "main"]).getLogger()
+  logger.debug( sys.argv )
+  listOptions = []
+  strCommand = None
+  if len(sys.argv) == 1:
+      usage()
+  else:
+    # read in the command
+    sys.argv.pop(0)
+    strCommand = sys.argv.pop(0)
+    #print("command is "+strCommand)
+    ### read in the options
+    listOptions = sys.argv[:]
+
+    ### read in the properties
+
+    #### dispatch the commands
+    if strCommand == "execute":
+        logger.debug("calling execute...")
+        execute(listOptions)
+    else:
+        usage()
+#-------------
+####################### Main Routine starts here ########################
+if __name__ == "main":
+    main()
+                                      
+
+
+

+        Constructor for OSBExecutor
+   
+        :param dictProps: 
+        """

+        DBWLSScheduler.__init__(self, dictProps)

+def usage():
+    """

+    s=[]

+    s.append("MODULE: " + moduleName)

+def test(listOptions):    
+    """
+    Test Funktion that instantiates a Logger and then Instantiates a Test Class.
+    We call the do() method of the test class and log some debug output.
+
+    :param listOptions: program args
+    """
+    logger = common.utilities.Logger([moduleName, "testbase"]).getLogger()
+    logger.debug("no test implemented ...")
+    logger.debug("leaving ...")
+#end def
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#    Private and Helper Function of this Modul
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+def getHealthState(state):
+    """
+    return the health state as String
+
+    :param state : the HealthState instance
+    :returns: WARNING, CRITICAL, FAILED, OVERLOADED or OK
+    """
+    if (state.getState() == HealthState.HEALTH_WARN):
+        return "WARNING"
+    elif(state.getState()== HealthState.HEALTH_CRITICAL):
+        return "CRITICAL"
+    elif(state.getState()== HealthState.HEALTH_FAILED):
+        return "FAILED"
+    elif(state.getState()== HealthState.HEALTH_OVERLOADED):
+        return "OVERLOADED"
+    else:
+        return "OK"
+#end if
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+def getMessageSeverity(state):
+    """
+    returns the message severity from health state
+
+    :param state; the HealthState instance
+    :returns: MessageSeverity.INFO, MessageSeverity.WARNING or MessageSeverity.ERROR
+    """
+    if (state.getState()== HealthState.HEALTH_OK):
+        return MessageSeverity.INFO
+    elif (state.getState()== HealthState.HEALTH_WARN):
+        return MessageSeverity.WARNING
+    else:
+        return MessageSeverity.ERROR;
+    #end if
+#end def
+
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#   Classes
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+class DBEvent(Event):
+    """
+    Event for DB Systel Monitoring, inherits scheduler.event.Event
+    """
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def __init__(self, filter, sub_origin, param_name, param_value, severity,  msg):
+        """
+        Constructor for DBMessage
+         
+        :param filter: a message filter
+        :param sub_origin: the name of the sub origin
+        :param param_name: parameter name
+        :param param_value: parameter value
+        :param severity: MessageSeverity
+        :param msg: text message
+        """
+        Event.__init__(self, msg)
+        self.logger = common.utilities.Logger([moduleName, "DBEvent"]).getLogger()
+        self.logger.debug("Constructor")
+        self.msg = msg
+        self.filter = filter
+        self.sub_origin = sub_origin
+        self.param_name = param_name
+        self.param_value = param_value
+        self.severity = severity
+        self.timestamp = Time.getTimeStamp()
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def getTimeStamp(self):
+        """
+        getter methode for the timestamp
+
+        :returns: the timestamp
+        """
+        return self.timestamp
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def getFilter(self):
+        """
+        getter method for the filter 
+
+        :returns: the filter
+        """
+        return self.filter
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def getSubOrigin(self):
+        """
+        getter method for the sub origin 
+
+        :returns: the filter
+        """
+        return self.sub_origin
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def getParamName(self):
+        """
+        getter method for the parameter name 
+
+        :returns: the parameter name
+        """
+        return self.param_name
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def getParamValue(self):
+        """
+        getter method for the parameter value
+
+        :returns: the parameter value
+        """
+        return self.param_value
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def getSeverity(self):
+        """
+        getter method for the message severity
+
+        :returns: the message severity
+        """
+        return self.severity
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def getEventType(self):
+        """
+        getEventType overwrites the parents getEventType 
+        implementation and is used to filter messages for
+        the DBEventHandler implementation
+        """
+        return "DBEvent"
+    #end if
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def toString(self):
+        """
+        toString is used from the EventHandler to log the
+        message content. It conrtains acomma separated list 
+        of strings : 
+        msg_txt,timestamp,hostname,filter,origin,sub_origin,param_name,param_value,severity
+
+        """
+        return Event.getEventText(self) + ',' + str(Event.getTimeStamp(self)) + ',' + self.filter + ',' + self.sub_origin + ',' + self.param_name + ',' + self.param_value + ',' + str(self.severity)
+    #end if
+
+#end class
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#   Main
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+def main():
+  """
+  parse the command line and execute the command
+
+  #### the 1st argument is this module
+  #### the 2nd argument should be the command
+  #### the 3rd argument is an options string
+  """
+  # Initialize a log4j Logger:
+  logger = common.utilities.Logger([moduleName, "main"]).getLogger()
+  logger.debug( sys.argv )
+  listOptions = []
+  strCommand = None
+  if len(sys.argv) == 1:
+      usage()
+  else:
+    # read in the command
+    sys.argv.pop(0)
+    strCommand = sys.argv.pop(0)
+    #print("command is "+strCommand)
+    ### read in the options
+    listOptions = sys.argv[:]
+
+    ### read in the properties
+
+    #### dispatch the commands
+    if strCommand == "test":
+        logger.debug("calling test...")
+        test(listOptions)
+    elif strCommand == "connect":
+        usage()
+    else:
+        usage()
+#-------------
+####################### Main Routine starts here ########################
+if __name__ == "main":
+    main()

+#!/usr/bin/env jython
+from java.lang import Object, Thread, System
+#from java.util import Calendar
+from java.io import File, FileOutputStream, PrintWriter
+import common.utilities
+from common.utilities import toBool
+import wlstModule as wl
+import sys, traceback
+#from common.testbase import TestBase,Message,MessageHandler
+from task import Task
+from event import Event
+from eventhandler import EventHandler
+from timer import Timer
+
+#===================================================
+# global variables
+#===================================================
+schedulerTimeFile="../scheduler.time"
+
+moduleName="scheduler.py"
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#    Usage function
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+def usage():
+    """
+    Print out a usage message for this module
+    """
+    s=[]
+    s.append("####################################################################################")
+    s.append("MODULE: " + moduleName)
+    s.append("        Module used to start monitoring weblogic runtime mbeans")
+    s.append("")
+    s.append("USAGE: wlst "+ moduleName+" command [Options]")
+    s.append("         ")
+    s.append("COMMANDS: execute ")
+    s.append("             Calls the execute Function which start the monitoring process")
+    s.append("         ")
+    s.append("EXAMPLES: java weblogic.WLST " + moduleName + " execute")
+    s.append("         ")
+    s.append("####################################################################################")
+    for item in s:
+        print item
+   #end for
+#end def
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#    Public Interface of this Module
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+def execute(listOptions):
+    """
+    execute Funktion that instantiates a Logger and 
+    then Instantiates the testcases
+    We call the run() method to execute all tests
+
+    :param listOptions: program args
+    """
+    logger = common.utilities.Logger([moduleName, "scheduler"]).getLogger()
+    logger.debug("entering ...")
+    logger.debug("Options : %s" % listOptions)
+    logger.debug("Options : %s" % listOptions)
+
+    logger.debug("load properties")
+    dictProps = common.utilities.loadProperties()
+    
+    # testfaelle laden...    
+    scheduler = Scheduler(dictProps)
+    scheduler.execute()
+#end def
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#    Private and Helper Function of this Modul
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+# CLASSES
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+class Scheduler:
+    """
+    This class is the main class for executing test environment
+    """
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def __init__(self, dictProps):
+        """
+        Constructor for the Executor
+     
+        :param dictProps: dict with properties from monitoring.properties file
+        """
+        self.logger = common.utilities.Logger([moduleName, "scheduler"]).getLogger()
+        self.logger.debug("Scheduler Constructor")
+        self.dictProps = dictProps
+        self.tasklist = []
+        self.eventHandler = []
+        self.initializeTasks()
+        self.initializeEventHandler()
+    #end
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def initializeTasks(self):
+        """
+        initialises test cases from properties
+        """
+        logger = common.utilities.Logger([moduleName, "scheduler"]).getLogger()
+        logger.debug("initialize ...")
+
+        if self.dictProps.has_key("scheduler.time.file"): 
+            self.schedulerTimeFile = self.getProperty("scheduler.time.file")
+        else:
+            logger.warn("No property scheduler.time.file found! Use \"scheduler.time\" as default for storing the current execution time")
+        #end if
+
+        wlstLogFile = self.getProperty("scheduler.wlst.logfile")
+        wl.redirect(wlstLogFile, "False")
+    #def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def initializeEventHandler(self):
+        """
+        initialises the EventHandlers
+        """
+        if (toBool(self.getProperty("scheduler.debugmessages"))):
+            self.addEventHandler(EventHandler())
+        #end if
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def getProperty(self, property):
+        """
+        returns a property
+
+        :param property: the property key
+        :returns: the property value
+        """
+        return self.dictProps[property]
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def addTask(self, task):
+        """
+        add a task instance in the task list
+
+        :param task: an instance from class process.task.Task
+        """
+        self.tasklist.append(task)
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def addEventHandler(self,  eventHandler):
+        """
+        add a MessageHandler for all test instance
+
+        :param msgHandler: a common.testbase.MessageHandler instance
+        """
+        self.eventHandler.append(eventHandler)
+        for task in self.tasklist:
+            task.addEventHandler(eventHandler)
+        #end for
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def sendEvent(self, event):
+        """
+        forwards an event to all registered event handlers
+
+        :param event : a message from class process.event.Event
+        """
+        for evtHandler in self.eventHandler:
+            evtHandler.sendEvent(event)
+        #end for
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def run(self):
+        """
+        executes the test for all test instances
+        """
+        for task in self.tasklist:
+            task.execute()
+        #end for
+    #end def
+
+    #----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def isInitialized(self):
+      return True
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def execute(self):
+        """
+        main method, used to execute the testcases in an endless loop
+        """
+        timer = Timer()
+        isInitialized = False
+        pausetime = int(self.getProperty("scheduler.pausetime")) * 1000
+        maxruns = 100
+        runs = 0
+        while 1:
+            try:
+                self.saveTime()
+                if (not isInitialized):
+                    isInitilialied = self.isInitialized()
+                    #try:
+                    #    wl.connect(username=self.getProperty("monitoring.wls.username"), 
+                    #             password=self.getProperty("monitoring.wls.password"), 
+                    #             url=self.getProperty("admin.url"), 
+                    #             timeout=self.getProperty("monitoring.jmx.timeout"))
+                    #    isConnected = True
+                    #except:
+                    #    self.sendMessage(self.getExecutionErrorMessage())
+                #end if
+                timer.start()
+                self.run()
+                timer.stop()
+                elapsed = timer.elapse()
+                self.logger.info('execution time= ' + str(elapsed) + ' ms')
+                runs += 1
+                self.logger.info('runs: '+str(runs)+'/'+str(maxruns))
+                if runs >= maxruns:
+                   self.logger.info('maxruns reached')
+                   System.exit(0)
+                sleeptime = pausetime - elapsed
+                if sleeptime > 0:
+                   self.logger.debug('sleeping: '+str(sleeptime) + ' ms');
+                   Thread.sleep(pausetime - elapsed)
+                else:
+                   self.logger.debug("Warning: sleeptime is zero or negative. If required, increase the scheduler.pausetime value in the monitoring.properties file");
+                #end if
+            except:
+                apply(traceback.print_exception, sys.exc_info())
+                wl.dumpStack()
+                wl.disconnect()
+                isConnected = False
+                Thread.sleep(pausetime)
+            #end try
+        #end while
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def saveTime(self):
+        """
+        save the last execiution tome in a file
+        """
+        file = File(self.schedulerTimeFile)
+        outputStream = FileOutputStream(file)
+        writer = PrintWriter(outputStream, True)
+        writer.print(System.currentTimeMillis())
+        writer.close();
+    #end def
+#end class
+
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#   Main
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+def main():
+  """
+  parse the command line and execute the command
+  #### the 1st argument is this module
+  #### the 2nd argument should be the command
+  #### the 3rd argument is an options string
+  """
+  logger = common.utilities.Logger([moduleName, "main"]).getLogger()
+  logger.debug( sys.argv )
+  listOptions = []
+  strCommand = None
+  if len(sys.argv) == 1:
+      usage()
+  else:
+    # read in the command
+    sys.argv.pop(0)
+    strCommand = sys.argv.pop(0)
+    #print("command is "+strCommand)
+    ### read in the options
+    listOptions = sys.argv[:]
+
+    ### read in the properties
+
+    #### dispatch the commands
+    if strCommand == "execute":
+        logger.debug("calling execute...")
+        execute(listOptions)
+    else:
+        usage()
+#-------------
+####################### Main Routine starts here ########################
+if __name__ == "main":
+    main()
+                                      
+
+

+

+        """

+        self.logger.debug("Task Constructor")
+        self.eventHandler = []
+        self.enabled = enabled
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def run(self):
+        """

+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def execute(self):
+        """
+        entry point for testing. if flag enabled is True, then it 
+        calls the run method, which implements the business 
+        logic for testing.  
+        """
+        self.logger.debug("Task.execute() entered...")
+        if (self.isEnabled()):
+            self.logger.debug("Task.execute() : test is enabled...")
+            self.run()
+        else:
+            self.logger.debug("Task.execute() : test is not enabled...")
+        #end if
+    #end def
+    
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def addEventHandler(self, eventHandler):
+        """
+        add a EventHandler 
+        :param eventhandler: instance of a EventHandler class
+        """
+        self.logger.debug("Task.addEventHandler entered...")
+        self.eventHandler.append(eventHandler)
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def sendEvent(self, event):
+        """
+        forwards a message to all registered EventHandler instances
+
+        :param msg: a event class instance
+        """
+        self.logger.debug("Task.log() entered...")
+        if (len(self.eventHandler) > 0):
+            for eventhandler in self.eventHandler:
+                eventhandler.sendEvent(event)
+            #end for
+        else:
+            self.logger.error("Task.sendEvent() : no EventHandler registered...")
+        #end if
+    #end def 
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def isEnabled(self):
+        """
+        return the state of the enabled flag
+
+        :returns: True if monitoring is enabled, otherwise False
+        """
+        self.logger.debug("Task.isEnabled() entered...")
+        return self.enabled

+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def setEnabled(self, enabled):
+        """
+        set the enabled flag 
+    
+        :param enabled: boolean flag to enable or disable the message forwarding

+        self.enabled = enabled

+    ### read in the options

+        test(listOptions)
+    elif strCommand == "connect":
+        usage()
+    else:
+        usage()
+#-------------
+####################### Main Routine starts here ########################
+if __name__ == "main":
+    main()

+#!/usr/bin/env jython
+##
+# Template Module for Python to create ohter modules
+##
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#    Imports
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+import sys
+import common.utilities
+import wlstModule as wl
+
+from scheduler.event import Event
+from scheduler.eventhandler import EventHandler
+from wlstask import WLSTask
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#    Global variables
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+moduleName="wlsservertask.py"
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#    Usage function
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+def usage():
+    """
+    Print out a usage message for this module
+    """
+    s=[]
+    s.append("####################################################################################")
+    s.append("MODULE: " + moduleName)
+    s.append("        Module to use as a templte")
+    s.append("")
+    s.append("USAGE: wlst "+ moduleName+" command [Options]")
+    s.append("         ")
+    s.append("COMMANDS: test [options1 options2]")
+    s.append("             Calls a Test Function which in turn calls a Test class. Logging Debug-Output")
+    s.append("         ")
+    s.append("         ATTRIBUTS: option1 - just an options that will be printed")
+    s.append("                     option2 - just another option that will be printed")
+    s.append("                     ")
+    s.append("         ")
+    s.append("EXAMPLES: sh startWLST.sh wlsetup/"+moduleName+" 'test option1 option2'")
+    s.append("         ")
+    s.append("####################################################################################")
+    for item in s:
+        print item
+   #end for
+#end def
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#    Public Interface of this Module
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+def test(listOptions):
+    """
+    Test Funktion that instantiates a Logger and then Instantiates a Test Class.
+    We call the do() method of the test class and log some debug output.
+  
+    :param listOptions: program args
+    """
+    logger = common.utilities.Logger([moduleName, "test"]).getLogger()    
+    logger.debug("entering ...")
+    logger.debug("Options : %s" % listOptions)
+    logger.debug("load properties")
+    dictProps = common.utilities.loadProperties()
+
+    logger.debug("now connect to the admin server...")
+    wl.connect(username=dictProps["monitoring.wls.username"], password=dictProps["monitoring.wls.password"], url=dictProps["admin.url"])
+
+    testclass = WLSServerTask(true)
+    testclass.addEventHandler(EventHandler())
+    testclass.execute()
+    testclass.sendEvent(Event("test"))
+    logger.debug("leaving ...")
+#end def
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#    Private and Helper Function of this Modul
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#----------------------------------------------------------------
+#   Classes
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+class WLSServerTask(WLSTask):
+    """
+    This class inherits the common.testbase.TestBase Class and is used to 
+    as an abstract class for monitoring the ServerRuntime MBean. Child classes 
+    has to overwrite the serverTest() to implement the buisiness logic for 
+    monitoring a given resource 
+    """
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def __init__(self, enabled):
+        """
+        Constructor for the ServerTest
+ 
+        :param enabled: True, messages are forwarded to a messagehandler, otherwise false
+        """
+
+        WLSTask.__init__(self, enabled)
+        self.logger = common.utilities.Logger([moduleName, "WLSServerTask"]).getLogger()
+        self.logger.debug("Constructor")
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def wlsserver_execute(self, server):
+        """
+        this method is used to test the servers runtimebeans.
+        the method just returns the servers ServerRuntimeMBean and
+        must be overwritten in child classes, to implement the monitoring 
+        of the servers mbeans.
+
+        :param server: the server name
+   
+        :returns: the ServerRuntimeMBean for a given server, or None, if the server is not running
+        """
+        self.logger.debug("WLSServerTask.wlsserver_execute: just entered...")
+        serverRuntimes=wl.domainRuntimeService.getServerRuntimes();
+        return self._getServerRuntime(serverRuntimes, server)
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def run(self):
+        """
+        the run method inherits the WLSTask.run() method.
+        it loads all configured servers first, using the
+        wl.domainconfig mbeans. Next it iterates over all servers
+        and execute the wlsserver_execute() method, which has to implement the
+        business logic to access the servers runtime mbeans 
+        """
+        self.logger.debug("WLSServerTask.run(): just entered...")
+        # returns all Servers of the domaene
+        self.logger.debug("execute: load domain config ...")
+        wl.domainConfig()
+        servers = wl.cmo.getServers()
+
+        # call super execute to initialize the domain runtime
+        self.logger.debug("execute: call execute() from to initialize the domainruntme ...")
+        WLSTask.run(self)
+        for server in servers:
+            self.logger.debug( 'now checking' + server.getName())            
+            self.wlsserver_execute(server.getName())
+        #end for
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def _getServerRuntime(self, serverRuntimes, server):
+        """
+        this private method is used from the wlsserver_execute() method to 
+        return the server runtime mbean for a given server
+
+        :param serverRuntimes: an array of ServerRuntimeMBeans
+        :param server: the server name
+ 
+        :returns: the ServerRuntimeMBean for a given server
+        """
+        self.logger.debug("getServerRuntime")
+        for i in range(0, len(serverRuntimes)):
+            serverRuntime = serverRuntimes[i];
+            if (serverRuntime.getName() == server):
+                self.logger.debug("return" + str(serverRuntime.getName()))
+                return serverRuntime;
+            #end if
+        #end for
+        self.logger.debug("return None")
+        return None;
+    #end def
+
+#end class
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#   Main
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+def main():
+  """
+  parse the command line and execute the command
+  #### the 1st argument is this module
+  #### the 2nd argument should be the command
+  #### the 3rd argument is an options string
+  """
+  logger = common.utilities.Logger([moduleName, "main"]).getLogger()
+  logger.debug( sys.argv )
+  listOptions = []
+  strCommand = None
+  if len(sys.argv) == 1:
+      usage()
+  else:
+    # read in the command
+    sys.argv.pop(0)
+    strCommand = sys.argv.pop(0)
+    #print("command is "+strCommand)
+    ### read in the options
+    listOptions = sys.argv[:]
+
+    ### read in the properties
+
+    #### dispatch the commands
+    if strCommand == "test":
+        logger.debug("calling test...")
+        test(listOptions)
+    elif strCommand == "connect":
+        usage()
+    else:
+        usage()
+#-------------
+####################### Main Routine starts here ########################
+if __name__ == "main":
+    main()

+

+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+def usage():
+    """
+    Print out a usage message for this module
+    """
+    s=[]
+    s.append("####################################################################################")
+    s.append("MODULE: " + moduleName)
+    s.append("        Module to use as a templte")
+    s.append("")
+    s.append("USAGE: wlst "+ moduleName+" command [Options]")
+    s.append("         ")
+    s.append("COMMANDS: test [options1 options2]")
+    s.append("             Calls a Test Function which in turn calls a Test class. Logging Debug-Output")
+    s.append("         ")
+    s.append("         ATTRIBUTS: option1 - just an options that will be printed")
+    s.append("                     option2 - just another option that will be printed")
+    s.append("                     ")
+    s.append("         ")
+    s.append("EXAMPLES: sh startWLST.sh wlsetup/"+moduleName+" 'test option1 option2'")
+    s.append("         ")
+    s.append("####################################################################################")
+    for item in s:
+        print item
+   #end for
+#end def
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#    Public Interface of this Module
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+def test(listOptions):
+    """
+    Test Funktion that instantiates a Logger and then Instantiates a Test Class.
+    We call the do() method of the test class and log some debug output.
+  
+    :param listOptions: program args
+    """
+	logger = common.utilities.Logger([moduleName, "serviceActivation"]).getLogger()
+	logger.debug("test is not supported...")
+#end def
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#    Private and Helper Function of this Modul
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#   Classes
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+class ServiceActivation(Object):
+    """
+    the ServiceActivation Class is used to enable or
+    disable services in OSB
+    """
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def __init__(self, host, port, username, password, enable):	
+        """
+        Constructor for the ServiceActivation class
+     
+        :param host: the OSB hostname
+        :param port: the OSB port
+        :param username: the OSB username
+        :param password: the OSB password
+	  :param enabled : True if services should be activated, False to dectivate them
+        """
+        self.logger = common.utilities.Logger([moduleName, "ServiceActivation"]).getLogger()
+        self.logger.debug("ServiceActivation Constructor")
+        self.isEnabled=enable
+        self.hostname=host
+        self.port=port
+        self.username=username
+        self.password=password
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def enableServices(self, configMBean, proxyServiceConfigurationMBean, businessServiceConfigurationMBean):
+        """
+        the enableService method is executed from the activate method and 
+        used to activate or deactivate a service
+
+        :param configMBean: the ALSBConfigurationMBean from OSB
+        :param proxyServiceConfigurationMBean: the ProxyServiceConfigurationMBean from OSB
+        :param businessServiceConfigurationMBean: the BusinessServiceConfigurationMBean from OSB
+        """
+        refs = configMBean.getRefs(Ref.DOMAIN)
+        refsList = ArrayList()
+        refsList.addAll(refs)
+ 
+        for ref in refsList :
+            if ref.getTypeId() == "ProxyService" :
+                if self.isEnabled == true:
+                    self.logger.debug("enabling for " + ref.getFullName())
+                    proxyServiceConfigurationMBean.enableMonitoring(ref)
+                else:
+                    self.logger.debug("disabling for " + ref.getFullName())
+                    proxyServiceConfigurationMBean.disableMonitoring(ref)
+                #end if
+            elif ref.getTypeId() == "BusinessService" :
+                if self.isEnabled == true:
+                    self.logger.debug("enabling for " + ref.getFullName())
+                    businessServiceConfigurationMBean.enableMonitoring(ref)
+                else:
+                    self.logger.debug("disabling for " + ref.getFullName())
+                    businessServiceConfigurationMBean.disableMonitoring(ref) 
+                #end if
+            #end if
+        #end for
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def activate(self):
+        """
+        the activate() methoid is the main entry point for activation or deactivation 
+        proxyservices and businessservices in osb. It connects to a running OSB domain,
+        loads the ALSConfigurationMBean, the businessServiceConfigurationMBean and the
+        ProxyServiceConfigurationMBean and calls the enableService method() to activate
+        or deactivate a service
+        """
+        sessionName = "ServiceActivation"
+        serviceURL=JMXServiceURL("t3", self.hostname, int(self.port), "/jndi/" + DomainRuntimeServiceMBean.MBEANSERVER_JNDI_NAME)
+        h=Hashtable()
+        h.put(Context.SECURITY_PRINCIPAL, self.username)
+        h.put(Context.SECURITY_CREDENTIALS, self.password)
+        h.put(JMXConnectorFactory.PROTOCOL_PROVIDER_PACKAGES, "weblogic.management.remote")
+
+        conn = JMXConnectorFactory.connect(serviceURL, h)
+        mbconn = conn.getMBeanServerConnection()
+        sm = JMX.newMBeanProxy(mbconn, ObjectName.getInstance(SessionManagementMBean.OBJECT_NAME), SessionManagementMBean)
+
+        sm.createSession(sessionName)
+        configMBean = JMX.newMBeanProxy(mbconn, ObjectName.getInstance("com.bea:Name=" + ALSBConfigurationMBean.NAME + "." + sessionName + ",Type=" + ALSBConfigurationMBean.TYPE), ALSBConfigurationMBean)
+        domainService = weblogic.management.jmx.MBeanServerInvocationHandler.newProxyInstance(mbconn, ObjectName(DomainRuntimeServiceMBean.OBJECT_NAME), DomainRuntimeServiceMBean, false)
+
+        proxyServiceConfigurationMBean = domainService.findService(String("ProxyServiceConfiguration.").concat(sessionName),'com.bea.wli.sb.management.configuration.ProxyServiceConfigurationMBean', None)
+        businessServiceConfigurationMBean = domainService.findService(String("BusinessServiceConfiguration.").concat(sessionName),'com.bea.wli.sb.management.configuration.BusinessServiceConfigurationMBean', None)
+
+        self.enableServices(configMBean, proxyServiceConfigurationMBean, businessServiceConfigurationMBean)
+
+        sm.activateSession(sessionName, "Complete enable/disable services")
+        conn.close()
+    #end def
+#end class
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#   Main
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+def main():
+  """
+  parse the command line and execute the command
+  #### the 1st argument is this module
+  #### the 2nd argument should be the command
+  #### the 3rd argument is an options string
+  """
+  logger = common.utilities.Logger([moduleName, "main"]).getLogger()
+  logger.debug( sys.argv )
+  listOptions = []
+  strCommand = None
+  if len(sys.argv) != 6:
+      usage()
+  else:
+    # read in the command
+    sys.argv.pop(0)
+    strCommand = sys.argv.pop(0)
+    #print("command is "+strCommand)
+    ### read in the options
+    listOptions = sys.argv[:]
+
+    ### read in the properties
+    host = listOptions[0]
+    port = listOptions[1]
+    username = listOptions[2]
+    password = listOptions[3]
+
+    #### dispatch the commands
+    if strCommand == "test":
+        logger.debug("calling test...")
+        test(listOptions)
+    elif strCommand == "activate":            
+        sa = ServiceActivation(host, port, username,password, true)
+        sa.activate()
+    elif strCommand == "deactivate":
+        sa = ServiceActivation(host, port, username,password, false)
+        sa.activate()
+    else:
+        usage()
+#-------------
+####################### Main Routine starts here ########################
+if __name__ == "main":
+    main()

+    """
+    Utility function, used to return the health state as String
+
+    :param state: the HealthState
+    :returns: WARNING, CRITICAL, FAILED, OVERLOADED or OK
+    """
+    if (state.getState() == HealthState.HEALTH_WARN):
+        return "WARNING";
+    elif(state.getState()== HealthState.HEALTH_CRITICAL):
+        return "CRITICAL";
+    elif(state.getState()== HealthState.HEALTH_FAILED):
+        return "FAILED";
+    elif(state.getState()== HealthState.HEALTH_OVERLOADED) :
+        return "OVERLOADED";
+    else:
+        return "OK";
+    #end if
+#end def
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+def usage():
+    """
+    Print out a usage message for this module
+    """
+    s=[]
+    s.append("####################################################################################")
+    s.append("MODULE: " + moduleName)
+    s.append("        Module to use as a templte")
+    s.append("")
+    s.append("USAGE: wlst "+ moduleName+" command [Options]")
+    s.append("         ")
+    s.append("COMMANDS: test [options1 options2]")
+    s.append("             Calls a Test Function which in turn calls a Test class. Logging Debug-Output")
+    s.append("         ")
+    s.append("         ATTRIBUTS: option1 - just an options that will be printed")
+    s.append("                     option2 - just another option that will be printed")
+    s.append("                     ")
+    s.append("         ")
+    s.append("EXAMPLES: sh startWLST.sh wlsetup/"+moduleName+" 'test option1 option2'")
+    s.append("         ")
+    s.append("####################################################################################")
+    for item in s:
+        print item
+   #end for
+#end def
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#    Public Interface of this Module
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+def test(listOptions):
+    """
+    Test Funktion that instantiates a Logger and then Instantiates a Test Class.
+    We call the do() method of the test class and log some debug output.
+
+    :param listOptions: program args
+    """
+    logger = common.utilities.Logger([moduleName, "test"]).getLogger()    
+    logger.debug("entering ...")
+    logger.debug("Options : %s" % listOptions)
+    logger.debug("load properties")
+    dictProps = common.utilities.loadProperties()
+
+    logger.debug("now connect to the admin server...")
+    wl.connect(username=dictProps["monitoring.wls.username"], password=dictProps["monitoring.wls.password"], url=dictProps["admin.url"])
+
+    applications = dictProps['monitoring.deployments.names']
+    testclass = ApplicationRuntimeTask(True,applications)
+    testclass.addEventHandler(EventHandler())
+    testclass.execute()
+    testclass.sendEvent(Event("test"))
+    logger.debug("leaving ...")
+#end def
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#    Private and Helper Function of this Modul
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#   Classes
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+class ApplicationRuntimeTask (WLSServerTask):
+    """
+    This class is used to test the ApplicationRuntimes. Inherits the
+    ServerTest class
+    """
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def __init__(self, enabled, applications):
+        """
+        Constructor for the ApplicationRuntimeTask. Inherits the ServerTest class
+         
+        :param enabled: if True, test is enabled, if False not
+        :param applications: a comma-separated list of  applications, which should NOT be tested
+        """
+        WLSServerTask.__init__(self, enabled)
+        self.logger = common.utilities.Logger([moduleName, "ApplicationRuntimeTask"]).getLogger()
+        self.logger.debug("ApplicationRuntimeTask Constructor")
+        self.applications = applications
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def wlsserver_execute(self,server):
+        """
+        test the servers application runtime mbean
+
+        :param server: the server name
+        """
+        self.logger.debug("ApplicationRuntimeTask: test " + server)
+        serverRuntime =  WLSServerTask.wlsserver_execute(self, server)
+        if (serverRuntime == None) :
+            self.logger.debug("ApplicationRuntimeTask: no server runtime found for " + server)
+            msg = "ApplicationRuntime health on server " + server + " is FAILED"
+            WLSServerTask.sendEvent(self, DBEvent("weblogic.deployments", server, server + ".HEALTH", "FAILED", MessageSeverity.ERROR, msg))
+        else:
+            self.logger.debug("ApplicationRuntimeTask: server runtime found for " + server)
+            applicationRuntimes = serverRuntime.getApplicationRuntimes()
+            for i in range(0, len(applicationRuntimes)):
+                applicationRuntimeName = applicationRuntimes[i].getName()
+                self.logger.debug("ApplicationRuntimeTask: verify " + applicationRuntimeName)
+                if (self.inApplications(applicationRuntimeName)):
+                    componentRuntimes = applicationRuntimes[i].getComponentRuntimes()
+                    for c in range (0, len(componentRuntimes)):
+                        cMBean = componentRuntimes[c]
+                        componentName = cMBean.getName()
+                        componentType = cMBean.getType()
+                            
+                        # checking the WebAppomponentRuntime always return 0 as state
+                        # this seems to be a bug, so we skip checking the state of
+                        # the WebAppComponentRuntime
+                        if ( not componentType == 'WebAppComponentRuntime'):
+                            state = cMBean.getDeploymentState()
+                            self.logger.debug("ApplicationRuntimeTask: verify component " + componentName +" ,type=" + componentType + ",State =" + str(state))         
+                            severity = MessageSeverity.INFO
+                            deploymentState = " ";
+                            if (state == cMBean.ACTIVATED):
+                                deploymentState = "ACTIVATED "
+                            elif (state == cMBean.NEW):
+                                deploymentState = "NEW"
+                                severity = MessageSeverity.ERROR                        
+                            elif (state == cMBean.PREPARED):
+                                deploymentState = "PREPARED "
+                                severity = MessageSeverity.ERROR
+                            elif (state == cMBean.UNPREPARED):
+                                deploymentState = "UNPREPARED "
+                                severity = MessageSeverity.ERROR
+                            #end if
+                            msg = "Application " + componentName + " is in deployment state " + deploymentState
+                            if ( not componentName == "ejb.jar" ) :
+                                WLSServerTask.sendEvent(self, DBEvent("weblogic.deployments", server, componentName, deploymentState, severity, msg))
+                            else:
+                                WLSServerTask.sendEvent(self, DBEvent("weblogic.deployments", server, applicationRuntimeName, deploymentState, severity, "Application " + applicationRuntimeName+" is in deployment state "+deploymentState))
+                            #end if
+                            if ( componentType == "EJBComponentRuntime") :
+                                self.testEJBRuntimes(server, cMBean)
+                            #end if
+                        #end if
+                    #end for
+                #end if
+            #end for
+        #end if
+        return serverRuntime
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def testEJBRuntimes(self,server, cMBean):    
+        """
+        test the ejb runtimes mbean for message driven beans.
+        all other ejbs will be ignored
+
+        :param server: the server name
+        :param cMBean: ComponentRuntime
+        """  
+        ejbRuntimes = cMBean.getEJBRuntimes()
+        for i in range(0, len( ejbRuntimes)):
+            ejbRuntime = ejbRuntimes[i]
+            ejbName = ejbRuntime.getName()
+            ejbType = ejbRuntime.getType()
+            
+            severity = MessageSeverity.INFO
+            healthString = "OK"
+            if (ejbType == "MessageDrivenEJBRuntime"):
+                health = ejbRuntime.getHealthState()
+                if ( not health.getState() == HealthState.HEALTH_OK):
+                    severity = MessageSeverity.ERROR
+                    healthString = getHealthState(health)
+                #end if
+                msg = "EJB " + ejbName + " is in health state " + healthString
+                WLSServerTask.sendEvent(self, DBEvent("weblogic.deployments.ejb", server, ejbName, healthString, severity, msg))
+            #end if
+        #end for
+    #end def
+
+    #-----------------------------------------------------------------
+    def inApplications(self, application):
+        """
+        returns true, if application is testable, or false if 
+        it should be ignored
+        see property monitoring.deployments.ignore
+
+        :param application: name of the applicaton
+        :returns: True, if application is testable, otherwise False
+        """
+        self.logger.debug("ApplicationRuntimeTask.inApplications() entered. Application = " + application)
+        if (self.applications != None and len(self.applications) > 0):
+            appnames = self.applications.split(",")
+            for app in appnames:
+                if (application.find(app) >= 0):
+                    self.logger.debug("ApplicationRuntimeTask.inApplications(), application will be tested. entry found in filter for " + application)
+                    return True
+                #end if
+            #end for
+            self.logger.debug("ApplicationRuntimeTask.inApplications(), no entry found in filter set. no test for " + application)
+            return False
+        else:
+            self.logger.debug("ApplicationRuntimeTask.inApplications(), no filter set defined, so return true for " + application)
+            return True
+        #end if
+    #end def
+
+#end class
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+#   Main
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+
+#-----------------------------------------------------------------
+def main():
+  """
+  parse the command line and execute the command
+  #### the 1st argument is this module
+  #### the 2nd argument should be the command
+  #### the 3rd argument is an options string
+  """
+  # Initialize a log4j Logger:
+  logger = common.utilities.Logger([moduleName, "main"]).getLogger()
+  logger.debug( sys.argv )
+  listOptions = []
+  strCommand = None
+  if len(sys.argv) == 1:
+      usage()
+  else:
+    # read in the command
+    sys.argv.pop(0)
+    strCommand = sys.argv.pop(0)
+    #print("command is "+strCommand)
+    ### read in the options
+    listOptions = sys.argv[:]
+
+    ### read in the properties
+
+    #### dispatch the commands
+    if strCommand == "test":
+        logger.debug("calling test...")
+        test(listOptions)
+    elif strCommand == "connect":
+        usage()
+    else:
+        usage()
+#-------------
+####################### Main Routine starts here ########################
+if __name__ == "main":
+    main()
